bitsby8 (3.0.0~alpha-1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Rename: the package, systemd unit, system user and all install paths
    move from `fdcsds` to `bitsby8` (/usr/lib, /etc, /var/lib, /var/log,
    /usr/share). The package declares Conflicts/Replaces/Provides: fdcsds so
    apt cleanly supersedes the old package on upgrade.
  * Migration: on upgrade from fdcsds, config under /etc/fdcsds is seeded
    into /etc/bitsby8 (preinst), and /var/lib/fdcsds + /var/log/fdcsds are
    moved to the bitsby8 paths with backward-compatibility symlinks left
    behind (postinst). The SQLite database (fdcplus.db) and runtime override
    file are renamed in-process on first startup.
  * A /usr/bin/fdcsds compatibility symlink is retained alongside
    /usr/bin/bitsby8.

 -- Joe Toppe <mreppot@gmail.com>  Mon, 20 Jul 2026 00:00:00 +0000

fdcsds (2.0.1-4) unstable; urgency=medium

  * MCP: HTTP transport support (SSE + streamable HTTP) alongside existing
    stdio transport.
  * Terminal: key-mapping settings modal with persistent configuration.
  * MCP: send_to_terminal now appends CR when text has no trailing newline.
  * Marked as `unstable` because this is a release candidate; will be
    promoted to `stable` for the 2.0.1 final tag.

